                            <p><strong>Top Performer:</strong> AuguStar Virtus IUL II shows the highest projected Account Value at Year 30 ($1,871,608), despite a higher initial death benefit.</p>
                            <p><strong>Runner-Up:</strong> F&G Pathsetter® is a close second, with strong long-term projections potentially driven by its higher illustrated rate (7.05%).</p>
                            <p><strong>Conclusion:</strong> For pure cash accumulation based on current illustrations, <strong>AuguStar</strong> and <strong>F&G</strong> appear to be the most efficient choices.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                 <!-- Income Efficiency -->
                <div class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-md border border-slate-200">
                    <button class="accordion-header w-full flex justify-between items-center p-5 text-left font-semibold text-lg text-slate-800 focus:outline-none">
                        <span>Income Efficiency & Safety</span>
                        <svg class="accordion-icon w-5 h-5" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 5l7 7-7 7"></path></svg>
                    </button>
                    <div class="accordion-content">
                        <div class="p-5 border-t border-slate-200 text-slate-700 space-y-3">
                            <p>While none of the policies illustrate a specific income stream, they are all designed to provide tax-advantaged income through loans.</p>
                            <p><strong>Standout Feature:</strong> The <strong>Mutual of Omaha</strong> policy includes a <strong>Lapse Guard</strong> rider. This is a critical feature for income strategies, as it helps prevent the policy from lapsing due to outstanding loans, which could otherwise create a significant taxable event.</p>
                            <p><strong>Conclusion:</strong> For clients prioritizing a safe and sustainable tax-free income stream, <strong>Mutual of Omaha</strong> offers a distinct advantage with its protective Lapse Guard rider.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                 <!-- Protection Efficiency -->
                <div class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-md border border-slate-200">
                    <button class="accordion-header w-full flex justify-between items-center p-5 text-left font-semibold text-lg text-slate-800 focus:outline-none">
                        <span>Protection Efficiency (Death Benefit & Riders)</span>
                        <svg class="accordion-icon w-5 h-5" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 5l7 7-7 7"></path></svg>
                    </button>
                    <div class="accordion-content">
                        <div class="p-5 border-t border-slate-200 text-slate-700 space-y-3">
                           <p><strong>Comprehensive Living Benefits:</strong> <strong>F&G Pathsetter®</strong> offers the most robust suite of no-cost Accelerated Benefit Riders, covering Critical, Chronic, and Terminal Illness, making it a strong choice for comprehensive health-related protection.</p>
                           <p><strong>Unique Downside Protection:</strong> <strong>Mutual of Omaha</strong> provides a unique <strong>Guaranteed Refund Option</strong>. This acts as a safety net, allowing the policyholder to get premiums back if the policy is surrendered after a certain period, protecting against poor market performance.</p>
                           <p><strong>Conclusion:</strong> For the broadest living benefit coverage, <strong>F&G</strong> is superior. For premium protection and downside risk mitigation, <strong>Mutual of Omaha's</strong> Guaranteed Refund Option is a compelling and unique feature.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
